notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-20T11:01:07.466Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented (test-only + CI, zero production change). Root cause confirmed: gate scripts are already Windows-correct (static-quality-gate normalizes reported paths via relativeToRepo; docs-skills-gate builds logical paths with path.posix) — only the specs mismatched native vs POSIX separators. Fixes per failure class: (1) static-quality-gate walkFiles/resolveRelativeImport/checkOrphanSourceModules use POSIX-keyed fs mocks against drive-lettered win32 candidates → new harness.mockPosixPath() forces node:path→path.posix in those 3 helper tests (inverse of runtime-schema-path-win32-guard); node:path added to harness builtinUnmocks. (2) docs-skills-gate collectMarkdownFiles readdir mock keyed on /docs → normalize dir separators in the mock. (3) bundle-cli + contracts-snapshot stringContaining path assertions → compare against path.join(...) (native per host). (4) smoke-npx-from-pack execFileSync mocks keyed on bare npm/npx but resolveCommand appends .cmd on win32 → baseCommand() strips .cmd in all mocks. Re-broadened per-PR windows-regression CI job to the full tests/unit/scripts/ directory and locked it in ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Verified on Linux: 4774 tests pass, coverage literal 100/100/100/100, quality:static + docs-skills + contracts + security:scan green, isolated temp-dir smoke (init/create/update/list/close/validate) clean. mockPosixPath forces POSIX on every host, so the Linux helper-test run faithfully reproduces the Windows path; the windows-regression job is the final oracle."
  "2026-06-20T11:18:37.425Z",claude-code-agent,"BROADENED windows-regression job (full tests/unit/scripts/) acted as the Windows oracle and exposed a SECOND class the original triage under-counted: 3 docs-skills-gate tests. Two were the same mocked-path separator class (readFile SKILL.md regex was forward-slash-only → normalized). The third (real-fs seeded-fixture full-mode) was a distinct LINE-ENDINGS class: with no .gitattributes, windows-latest checkout converts tracked text to CRLF, so the gate reads real SKILL.md as ---\\r\\n and extractFrontmatter's startsWith('---\\n') reports valid skills as missing frontmatter. Root-caused by Linux repro: win32-path mock alone produced 0 failures (path logic is fine), isolating CRLF as the cause. Fixed broadly via repo-root .gitattributes (text=auto eol=lf; 0 existing CRLF files → no churn) rather than per-test, since it eliminates the CRLF class for ALL real-file-reading specs on Windows. Production gate scripts unchanged."
  "2026-06-20T11:45:55.030Z",claude-code-agent,"Post-merge evidence: PR #317 merged to main (bdd745ee). Final CI run 27869792267 fully green — all 14 checks PASS incl Windows regression (Node 20, full tests/unit/scripts/ dir, job 82479802098), Gates(static) (changelog:pm:check now green after CHANGELOG regen), Gates(coverage) 100/100/100/100, typecheck/compat/smokes, CodeQL, Docs and Skills. Bots: Gemini reviewed clean (no findings); CodeRabbit check resolved pass with no actionable comments; Sourcery weekly rate-limited; Codex not connected. Telemetry stack healthy (all containers up, API ok v2026.6.20, RabbitMQ backlog 0, 12487 events/24h real-time). Sentry healthy: reachable, recent data through 2026-06-13, PII scrubbing verified ([scrubbed_path]), 0 fatal/critical issues (gate-blocking class clean)."
